              {
                "type": "Words",
                "data": {
                  "value": "According to this definition v[i] >= 0 for all i. It differs from the definition in paper [1]_ (eq. (2.2)), where the absolute value of v is used. Both definitions are equivalent down the line. Derivatives of v with respect to x take value 1, -1 or 0 depending on a case."
                }
              }
